sentence.text: Variants of protein phosphorylation (lysine deficient protein kinase 1), desensitization of G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway by arrestin (b2 adrenergic receptor), regulation of membrane depolarization (ubiquitin-protein ligase NEDD4-like), regulation of systemic arterial blood pressure (kallikrein 1) contribute to hypertension, and protein import into nucleus, translocation (aldo-keto reductase family1 member C3), is associated with preeclampsia.
